

     
      "Nope.  And no clue where you'd find the old fart either.  I think he's been kicking around for ages, old Saint Ivan.  Haven't seen him in a long time now...hmmmm, yeah, go ask Yves about him.  You've got me curious...and you know what that means."  He turns back to the box.  "Are you a dragon?"  The creature looks up at him with an almost-smile and lets out a puff of flame that singes Litheroy's nose.  He leaps back with a yelp and you can't help but giggle.
     
    
